annotation.TEXT: The Circring Q9 from MM5 makes an appearance as a boss here. It doesn't move in a wavy pattern like it did in the original, and it has a few new motions to make the whole fight feel a lot different by comparison. With that being said, you can still cheese this thing by intentionally taking damage to bypass its hitbox and fire inside of it.

Despite being faster and having a different pattern, Big Pets really isn't that difficult of a boss. This is just another instance of me doing a terrible job. I think I may have actually broken the boss slightly as well (seeing how it magically pops back into existence when it goes into its final phase).

The Square Machine from MM4 makes a return here, only it's far more frustrating this time around due to even larger threats of instant death. You can still get crushed if you don't slide underneath the bottom piece, but the main eye will now shoot at you as the pieces go across the screen. If you get hit by this while sliding underneath the bottom piece, there's a very strong chance you'll get dragged to the edge of the screen and die.
I'm not even sure if using the Yamato Spear to skip these blocks is the most optimal way to bypass them. Either way, it's probably my favorite method.

The Rush Jet based path is a bit annoying (mainly due to the enemy placement), and I wouldn't really recommend taking it if you're just going to play this game casually. If you want the quickest route through this stage however, it's sadly your best option.
